FBIS4-66005 "drweu103aa_94014" FBIS-WEU-94-103 Daily Report 25 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS EU Supports Territorial Sovereignty of Ukraine EU Supports Territorial Sovereignty of Ukraine AU2505183094 Paris AFP in English 1734 GMT 25 May 94 AU2505183094 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Brussels, May 25 (AFP) -- The European Union [EU] Wednesday [25 May] issued a statement expressing full support for the territorial integrity of Ukraine, five days after the Crimean parliament adopted a separatist constitution. In the statement, the EU "expresses its grave concern at the recent developments in the Crimean region of Ukraine." "Noting that the situation has deteriorated over the past week and taking into consideration the decision of the Crimean parliament of May 20, it urges the continuation of efforts to find negotiated and legitimate solutions to the issue, without resort to confrontation or unilateral actions," the statement said. "The EU reiterates that an escalation of the conflict would have severe consequences for the stability in East Europe," it added.
